name: Around Football: Indonesian Poznan Dance
description:
Indonesian National Team was winning the game against Vanuatu, 6-0. So the supporters do the Poznan Dance as a banter. Poznan dance itself is a choreography of supporters where they turn their back toward the field, grabbing shoulders beside them, jumping around while chanting. Usually, they do this while the team that they support is winning with big margin.
